Context: The Office of Anti-Racism, Equity and Human Rights (OAREHRS) at George Brown College collaborates with various stakeholders to develop anti-racism resources. These resources include an anti-racism policy, training opportunities, and a "Take 5 for Anti-Racism" resource. The college offers a range of anti-racism training for participants, including online e-training. Nadia Richards serves as the Manager of Anti-Racism Integration at George Brown. In February, the college celebrated Black Futures and examined its anti-racism policies and practices with the help of a consulting firm. The Take 5 for Anti-Racism resource is designed to guide users through five steps to engage in Anti-Racism. Contact information: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca.
